cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a geometric problem of finding a non-crossing matching of a set of points in the plane that minimizes the length of the longest edge.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for computing bottleneck plane perfect matchings of different sizes.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization of finding a perfect matching.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with finding a matching that minimizes the length of the longest edge, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions that the problem of computing a bottleneck plane perfect matching is NP-hard.
